==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Waxbill
<hw>Wax"bill`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any one of numerous species of finchlike birds belonging to
<gen>Estrelda</gen> and allied genera, native of Asia, Africa, and
Australia. The bill is large, conical, and usually red in color,
resembling sealing wax. Several of the species are often kept as cage
birds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Waxbird</ent>⟦br⟧
